HEADWORD: Dehumanize
<hw>De*hu"man*ize</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <def>To divest of
human qualities, such as pity, tenderness, etc.; <as>as,
<ex>dehumanizing</ex> influences</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>dehumidify</ent>⟦br⟧
